'''GoGo Loco''' is a locomotion prefab, designed for [[avatars]] on the [[VRChat SDK]], and created to expand upon the default avatar controller. This tool also can be installed in avatar projects on the SDK, by using other third-party tools such as [[Community:VRCFury|VRCFury]]<ref>https://vrcfury.com/</ref> or [[Community:Modular Avatar|Modular Avatar]]<ref>https://modular-avatar.nadena.dev/</ref>.

== Overview ==
GoGo Loco expands on VRChat's avatar controller and inverse kinematics (IK), by providing access to implementing advanced toggles and animations for leg movements, jump animations, or poses for avatars in the VRChat SDK. 

=== Features ===
'''Avatar posing''' - avatars with GoGo Loco can be given several animations, for movement, sitting, and reclining.

'''Play space''' - avatars with GoGo Loco can also adjust their vertical height, giving the illusion of hovering, flying, or being beneath the ground.

=== Add-ons ===
'''GoGo Freeze''' - 'freezes' any animation or tracked movements that an avatar or user is making

'''GoGo Fly''' - adjusts collider settings on an avatar, giving an avatar the ability to fly, hover, and dash.

